                            responsible for executing instructions and powering through computations. In 2024, a
                            quad-core processor should be considered the baseline, with clock speeds ideally hovering
                            around 3.5 GHz or higher. Look for processors with efficient multi-threading capabilities to
                            handle modern game engines effectively.
